Arsenal Held 0-0 by Sunderland; West Ham Exits Relegation Zone; Villa Lose

-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 
2011-03-05T17:59:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-05/arsenal-held-0-0-by-sunderland-west-ham-exits-relegation-zone.html
Arsenal, second in English soccer’s
Premier League, drew 0-0 at home to Sunderland and moved to
within three points of leader  Manchester United .  Marouane Chamakh headed Jack Wilshere’s cross against the
crossbar after 75 minutes as Arsenal pushed for a win at its
Emirates Stadium.  Earlier, Sami Nasri’s freekick was pushed onto the crossbar
by Sunderland goalkeeper Simon Mignolet  Manchester United, which faces Liverpool tomorrow, has 60
points from 28 of 38 games. Arsenal has 57 points from 28 games.  West Ham beat Stoke 3-0 to move out of the three-team
relegation zone. Demba Ba, Manuel da Costa and Thomas Hitzlsperger scored at Upton Park.  West Bromwich Albion won 3-1 at Birmingham, which dropped
to third-bottom a week after beating Arsenal in the League Cup
final at Wembley stadium.  Goals from Youssouf Mulumbu, James Morrison and Paul Scharner gave  Roy Hodgson  his first win since becoming coach.
Jean Beausejour scored for Birmingham.  Bolton twice rallied to beat visiting Aston Villa 3-2.  Gary
Cahill  scored in each half for the host and Ivan Klasnic got the
winner four minutes before the end.  Villa had taken the lead with Darren Bent’s goal after 15
minutes and then with Marc Albrighton’s score.    Bobby Zamora , a second-half substitute, scored the winner
with a penalty a minute from the end as Fulham beat Blackburn 3-
2 at Craven Cottage.  Everton came back from a goal down to beat Newcastle 2-1
with Phil Jagielka’s score.    Manchester City  plays Wigan in the day’s late game.  To contact the reporters on this story:
